HEADWORD: Pierian
<hw>Pi*e"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Pierius</ets>, from Mount <etsep>Pierus</etsep>, in Thessaly,
sacred to the Muses.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Pierides or
Muses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Drink deep, or taste not the <qex>Pierian</qex> spring.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pierid</ent>⟦br⟧
